    <exercise number="15.1.49">
      <p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
          <li>
            <p>
              Which is easier, antidifferentiating <m>\dfrac{y}{1 + xy}</m> with respect to <m>x</m> or with respect to <m>y</m>? 
              Explain. 
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Evaluate <m>\ds \iint_\c{R} \dfrac{y}{1 + xy}\, dA</m>, where <m>\c{R} = [0,1] \times [0,1]</m>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
